---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "Support — Team Tally";
const description = "How to reach the team behind Team Tally and what to expect.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="support">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Team Tally</a>

      <h1>Support</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: May 11, 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          The fastest way to reach us is
          <a href="mailto:team-tally@eggo.is">team-tally@eggo.is</a>.
          Bug reports, feature requests, and "this saved my training group" stories all welcome.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What to expect</h2>
        <p>
          Team Tally is a small project, built and maintained outside business hours from
          Iceland. Every email is read; replies usually come within a few days, sometimes
          faster. Urgent issues (the app won't open, data is missing) are prioritised over
          feature requests.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Common questions</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Where is my data stored?</strong>
          Locally on your device, in a private SQLite database. Nothing is sent anywhere — no
          servers, no analytics, no backups. See the
          <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full story.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Can I sync between devices or share a team with co-captains?</strong>
          Not in this version. Team Tally is offline-first by design — one device is the
          source of truth. Multi-device sync is something we're considering for a future
          release; if it matters for your team, send a note to the email above so we can
          weigh it against other requests.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>How do I delete everything?</strong>
          Uninstall the app. The database lives in the app's sandbox, so removing the app
          removes every fine, player, and team setting along with it. There's no cloud copy.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Can I change the currency or team name after I've started?</strong>
          Yes — both live in the Settings tab and can be edited at any time without losing
          any data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Bug reports + feedback</h2>
        <p>
          When reporting an issue, including your device model, iOS version, and a short
          description of what you did before the bug appeared helps us reproduce and fix it
          faster. If the app crashes on launch, a screenshot of the error screen is the
          single most useful thing you can send.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .support {
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .back-link:hover {
      color: var(--primary);
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }
    .last-updated {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }
    section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--primary-light);
    }
    p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    a {
      color: var(--primary);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
